article.headline: Ferrari hits 10 3-pointers, scores 39 as Brown beats Dartmouth 89-67
article.description: — Kimo Ferrari sank a career-best 10 3-pointers and scored a career-high 39 points as Brown rolled to an 89-67 victory over Dartmouth on Saturday night.

article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- — Kimo Ferrari sank a career-best 10 3-pointers and scored a career-high 39 points as Brown rolled to an 89-67 victory over Dartmouth on Saturday night. Ferrari made 14 of 16 shots, missing just twice from beyond the arc for the Bears (11-17, 7-6 Ivy League). Ferrari, a senior, had a previous career high of 18 points just three games earlier. Nana Owusu-Anane totaled 13 points, eight rebounds and eight assists. Kino Lilly Jr. hit three 3-pointers and scored 13, adding eight assists and seven steals. Dusan Neskovic had 17 points to lead the Big Green (5-21, 1-12), who have lost nine in a row. Jayden Williams added 14 points and Romeo Myrthil scored 12. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
